/*---------------------------------------------------------------------------*\
  yang2020_Tg_polyethylene
  ========================
  ESTIMATE a polymer's GLASS-TRANSITION temperature Tg by the YANG 2020 modified
  group-contribution scheme -- the polymer sibling of the Joback small-molecule
  path, for Tg instead of density.  The repeat unit is decomposed into Yang's
  characteristic groups; each adds its limiting Tg contribution Yg(inf):

      M0      = sum n_i MW_i                 repeat-unit molar mass   [g/mol]
      Yg(inf) = sum n_i Yg_i(inf) (+ Nb*Ygb) limiting Tg function     [1e3 g.K/mol]
      Tg(inf) = Yg(inf) * 1e3 / M0           Tg at infinite Mw        [K]

  This is Yang 2020 -- NOT bare Van Krevelen.  The scheme predicts the INFINITE-
  Mw limit Tg(inf); the molecular-weight dependence Tg(Mn) = Tg(inf) - K/Mn is a
  later slice.

  SOURCE + LICENCE (the honest part):
    Yang, Zou, Ye, Zhu, Dong, Bi, ACS Omega 5 (2020) 19655,
    doi:10.1021/acsomega.0c04499 -- CC-BY 4.0, so the parameter values ARE
    redistributable.  Cited per value as "Yang 2020", never "Van Krevelen".

  >>> PROVISIONAL <<<  The Yang group VALUES are faithfully transcribed from SI
  Table S3, but the group<->structure mapping is drawn there as IMAGES; only the
  `CH2` group has an unambiguous SI text label, so this demo uses CH2 only (the
  polyethylene repeat unit -CH2-CH2-).  The full 58-group mapping needs human
  verification against the SI figures before promotion -- the values live in
  data/proposed/yang2020/ (UNVERIFIED tier), not data/standards/.

  THE GOLDEN: only M0 (an exact mass-balance fact) is checked.  Tg is SHOWN on
  the console (the machinery works) but NOT goldened as validated physics, since
  the mapping is provisional and PE's amorphous Tg is itself ill-defined.
\*---------------------------------------------------------------------------*/

operations
(
    {
        name        yang2020_Tg_polyethylene;
        type        estimateComponent;
        model       Yang2020;                // POLYMER-group estimator (Tg, CC-BY)
        component   polyethylene;

        // Repeat unit  -CH2-CH2-  :  two methylene groups (the one group whose
        // SI structure label is unambiguous).
        groups
        (
            { group CH2; count 2; }
        );

        // "See, then trust": the measured anchor (amorphous PE Tg is debated,
        // ~195-250 K; shown for context, not a tight target).
        reference
        {
            source   "amorphous polyethylene Tg (literature, debated ~195-250 K)";
            Tg       250.0;                  // K -- context only
        }

        // Opt-in PROMOTE: write a polymer repeat-unit proposal .dat.
        output  { proposal auto; }
    }
);
